doberman help i am a doberman owner for years i am married and have children and yrs we recently adopted an month nuetered male dobe a week ago i was told he was wonderful with children but coming from a home with an yr old lady she claimed he played with the nieghbor kids all the time he immediatley was wonderful with my husband and i it took about days for my current senior dobe and him to get along but he is terrified of my children if they are even in the same room he shakes pants and gets whale eyed i console him and slowly tried to introduce child at a time my oldest first he allowed my son to pet his head with my hand on his i slowly removed my hand he went to bite my son visciously not a nip it has been days and every eve my husband and i try to slowly get him close to my children my kids are being extremly patient but he still wants nothing to do w it he stays in the crate or in my bedroom with door locked unless walking him does he have any hope any suggestio i called an obedience trainer and am doing everything they are directing me to do he is such a loving dog with my husband and i i wish he could enjoy my children he would have a wonderful life with them sounds like you're one step ahead of where he needs to start have your kids in their rooms and settle in with your new dog to watch some tv with your husband arrange a time for one of the children to come through the room go to the kitchen and get a drink or something and then go back to their room tell them to not look at the dog don't make a big ruckus just enter the room and then exit do this several times for several nights if the dog is going to calm down around your children he will when he sees that they are not threatening once you make it to the point where he does not tremble pant or otherwise react negatively with them in the room then you can start having them direct attention toward him if after a week or two he shows no sign of improvement toward the children i might begin to think an adult only restrictive household is where he needs to be dobermans are notorious for anxiety and aggression when not properly socialized at a young age as he may not have been regardless of his previous owners' claims good luck Dog training Shaggy dog story The Shining (film) Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The Contender (television series) The Jazz Singer About a Boy The Brady Bunch Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Conspiracy (TNG episode) The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Dobermann Sin City EastEnders Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Social rule The Amber Spyglass The Death Gate Cycle Maison Ikkoku Milton H. Erickson Rose (Doctor Who) AFI 100 Years series G-Man (Half-Life) Housebreaking RuneScape quests Vegeta Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Father's Day (Doctor Who) National Football League Mickey Mouse Doctor Who (Enemy Within) The Inside The Empty Child Ferret Humphrey Bogart Hikikomori Traumatic brain injury StarCraft: Uprising The Critic Hip hop collaborations Poker jargon The Time Machine The Ashlee Simpson Show Kim Possible James Hanratty Aerial (dance move) Obedience training Garfield Avenue Q Columbine High School massacre New York Giants Ocean's Twelve The Star Wars Holiday Special Trailer Park Boys Kender Beetle in an Anthill The Apprentice 2 Trapped in the Closet The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Tenshinhan The Doctor Dances Pet skunk Jam (TV series) The Parting of the Ways The Family from One End Street Episodes of Lost (Season 2) The Fairly OddParents The Keeper of Traken The Dalek Invasion of Earth Laura Schlessinger Too Short a Season (TNG episode) Urinary incontinence Dog agility Symbiosis (TNG episode) The Adventures of Pete & Pete The Sims 2 Russian joke Lucille Ball Domestic rabbit Ben Johnson (athlete) Kodocha Situation comedy Clinical depression Friends Futurama (TV series - season 5) Salad Fingers The Big Goodbye (TNG episode) Ranma __ characters Marching band German Shepherd Dog Autism Characters of Lost Fancy rat Japanese te